```sh
git branch -v --all --format='%(refname:short)	%(objectname:short)	%(committerdate:short)	%(subject)'
```

Custom delimiter (e.g., pipe |):

```sh
git branch -v --all --format='%(refname:short)|%(objectname:short)|%(committerdate:iso)|%(subject)'
```

Useful format placeholders:
- %(refname:short) - branch name
- %(refname:lstrip=2) - strip "refs/heads/" prefix
- %(objectname:short) - short commit hash
- %(objectname) - full commit hash
- %(upstream:short) - tracking remote branch
- %(committerdate:short) - date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- %(committerdate:iso) - ISO 8601 date
- %(subject) - commit message subject
- %(authorname) - author name
